            <title>[FLINK-22725] SlotManagers should unregister metrics at the start of suspend()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-22725</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Slotmanagers register metrics in start(), but only unregister them in close().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This has 2 issues:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a) If the SM is restarted it cannot re-register the metrics because the old ones are still present; this isn&apos;t a critical problem (because the old ones still work) but it produces unnecesasry logging noise&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b) The metric may produce an NPE when accessed by a reporter during suspend().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
